Young Local Musicians: H-How's Taiga doing this...?!
Young Local Musicians: This is so awesome...! I've never heard anyone sing like this before!
Young Local Musicians: Taiga! Taiga! Taiga!
Arata: Huff... Huff... Huff... Huff...
Arata: Argh... Why...? Why can't I get any closer...?!
An: (Arata...)
Taiga: Arata, do you truly believe what you said earlier?
Arata: What?
Taiga: Are you really carrying Soma's hopes and dreams for him?
Arata: O-Of course I am! I'm doing everything I can for him!
Taiga: I also lost a dear friend and sister when Nagi passed away. So I sort of understand how you feel.
Taiga: I could kick and scream all I wanted, but she was never coming back. I've felt that loss...
Arata: ...
Taiga: And you're a better performer than just about everyone around here. No, I'd be hard-pressed to find another person as talented as you anywhere.
Taiga: But you're still singing with your eyes closed. You're not seeing this place, this audience.
Arata: What...?
Taiga: So, Arata, let me ask you this. Who are you really singing for?
Taiga: You're not trying to make Soma's dreams come true. You can't face the pain of having lost him, so you're just clinging to his dreams.
Taiga: Am I wrong...?
Arata: ...!
Arata: No... You're wrong!
Arata: I'm chasing this dream for Soma...!
Taiga: ... I've been down that path before.
Taiga: So, I'll ask you again. Arata, aren't you just singing for your own sake?
Arata: No! I... I...!!!
Arata: I-I'm...
